<2ND_LINE>AM-Trooper Shot,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>State Trooper Shot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WACO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state trooper was shot in the head Friday
night when he responded to a request for help from a sheriff's
department, the Texas Department of Public Safety said.
   David Shawn of Waco was in critical condition at Providence
Hospital in the central Texas city, a spokeswoman said.
   Shawn was shot about 9:30 p.m. when he responded to a McLennan
County sheriff's department call for assistance at Lincoln City, an
unincorporated community near Northcrest, a Waco suburb, the DPS
said.
   One person was arrested and DPS officials said another person
might have been involved.
   Law enforcement agencies began an extensive search, involving
about 200 officers, for the second person, said DPS spokesman Mike
Cox in Austin.
   The initial call from the sheriff's office involved a report of a
man with a gun drawn, authorities said.
</TEXT>
