<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Hungary-ThemePark     12-17 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Hungary-Theme Park,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Communist World's First Large Theme Park By 1993</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A theme park dubbed the Communist
world's first Disneyland will be built near Budapest by a joint
Austrian-Hungarian venture, the state MTI news agency reported.
   The Fanni-World company in Vienna and the Hungarian government
have signed a ``declaration of intention'' in Budapest whereby the
Austrian side would contribute $50 million or 70 percent of the
amount needed for the venture, MTI said Friday.
   The Hungarian side is to pay another $20 million for the park,
the report said. It said organizers planned to scour the Asian
market for other capital needed to complete the project, but it did
not say how much more will be needed.
   The park is scheduled for completion by 1993.
   The Marxist-oriented park will be ``an educational, as well as
recreational complex'' with the equipment to be imported from U.S.,
French, Japanese and Hong Kong firms, MTI said, without elaborating.
   The park is planned eight miles from downtown Budapest.
   In recent years, about 12 million tourists visited Hungary
anually and organizers expect the facility to be toured by 30,000
people a day when completed, the news agency said.
</TEXT>
