<HEAD>Soviets Conduct Underground Nuclear Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union conducted an underground nuclear
test today at government grounds near Semipalatinsk in Central Asia,
the official news agency Tass said.
   It said the 7:18 a.m. test (11:18 p.m. EST Friday) had a yield of
20 to 150 kilotons and was conducted ``with a view to upgrading
military technology.''
   Tass added, ``The radiation situation in the testing area and
beyond the test site is normal.''
   No other details were provided.
