<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0403</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Across Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow showers stretched from North Dakota to Ohio and from
Minnesota to Missouri today as rain and snow fell over sections of
California.
   There were snow showers in eastern North Dakota, northern
Minnesota, northwest Wisconsin, Michigan, Illinois, Indiana, western
Ohio, northeast Missouri and southern Iowa.
   Winter storm watches warning of possibly heavy local snow were
posted through tonight in northeast and north central Ohio, and from
northern New Jersey to southeast New York state, including Long
Island, and the southern half of New England. Winter storm watches
for tonight and Sunday were issued for east central New York and
much of Vermont.
   Rain, with snow in higher elevations, fell over central and
southwestern California today. Snow advisories were in effect for
the mountains and deserts of Southern California.
   Today's forecast called for snow from Michigan and northern
Illinois to the lower Great Lakes region, the Ohio Valley, the
northern and central Appalachians and the Atlantic Coast from New
Jersey to New England; and rain in southwestern California, becoming
snow in higher elevations in the Southwest.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 30s and 40s from Maryland
to North Carolina, the Tennessee Valley, Arkansas, the rest of the
northern and central Plains and the Rockies; near 70 degrees across
southern Florida; in the low 70s from southern Arizona to southeast
California; and the 50s and 60s in the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 9
degrees below zero at Houlton and Limestone, Maine, to 69 degrees at
Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 28 fair; Buffalo 19 cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 31
foggy; Cincinnati 24 snow; Cleveland 18 snow; Detroit 17 snow; New
York 24 snow; Philadelphia 22 cloudy; Pittsburgh 19 snow; Portland,
Maine 7 partly cloudy; Washington 25 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 21 fair; Chicago 14 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 38
fair; Denver 27 fair; Des Moines 19 fair; Indianapolis 23 snow;
Kansas City 24 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 17 fair; Nashville 27
fair; New Orleans 35 fair; St. Louis 30 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 34 partly cloudy; Anchorage 35 cloudy; Las
Vegas 44 fair; Los Angeles 53 fair; Phoenix 62 partly cloudy; Salt
Lake City 20 fair; San Diego 55 cloudy; San Francisco 48 cloudy;
Seattle 33 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 5 partly cloudy; Toronto 16 foggy.
