<HEAD>Passengers Lock Man in Jetliner's Bathroom</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORRISVILLE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man aboard an American Airlines jet
tried to enter the cockpit and then locked himself in a bathroom
while other passengers held the door shut, officials said Saturday.
   The Boeing 727, carrying 113 passengers from Dallas-Fort Worth to
Newark, N.J., was diverted Friday night to Raleigh-Durham
International Airport, where police arrested Claude Saint-Leger,
said Teresa Damiano, airport public affairs manager.
   Saint-Leger, 54, of Los Angeles, was charged with assault on an
airport police officer and was held in the Wake County jail, Ms.
Damiano said. No federal charges have been filed yet.
   The FBI interrogated Saint-Leger and other passengers before
allowing the flight to continue to Newark, Ms. Damiano said.
   ``The passenger was not armed or dangerous in any way according
to the police report,'' Ms. Damiano said. ``He just appeared to be
disturbed.''
