<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--PlaneFound     12-17 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Plane Found,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>World War II German Fighter Plane In Shrimp Trawl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Norwegians trawling for shrimps in the
North Sea caught a World War II German Messerschmitt ME-109 fighter
plane, the national NTB news agency reported Saturday.
   The agency, quoting a report in the daily Stavanger Aftenblad,
said the fishermen were about 340 miles south of Oslo on Thursday
when their trawl got stuck.
   ``In the trawl was a ME-109 fighter which must have rested on the
seabed for more than 40 years. The wings are hardly damaged, with
its Iron Cross marks still clearly visible. The front of the cabin
is smashed but the pilot's seat and machinegun are intact,'' the
report said.
   ME-109s were widely used by the German Luftwaffe during World War
II.
