<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--TigerAttack     12-17 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Tiger Attack,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tiger Attacks Handler At Sydney Zoo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tiger mauled a handler at Sydney's
Taronga Park Zoo on Saturday, leaving her in critical condition.
   Victoria Scrivener, 33, was rushed to the hospital with severe
injuries to her head and upper body after being attacked when she
apparently tried to separate the female Sumatran tiger from her cubs.
   A spokesman for the zoo, who declined to be identified, said the
zoo was investigating the incident.
   Dr. James Rogers, acting medical superintendent for the Royal
North Shore Hospital, said Ms. Scrivener was in critical condition
Saturday night.
   A colleague who entered the tiger cage with her was not hurt,
according to the zoo spokesman. He refused to comment further and
said the findings of the inquiry would not be available for some
time.
</TEXT>
