<2ND_LINE>AM-Father Arrested,0211</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Father Accused Of Killing Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>METAIRIE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who pleaded tearfully on television
four months ago for the safe return of his missing 11-year-old
daughter has been arrested in her death, authorities said.
   Gerald Estrade, a 32-year-old postal carrier, was arrested Friday
night on a charge of first-degree murder and was ordered held
without bond, said Jefferson Parish Sheriff Harry Lee.
   ``He was a suspect all along. From the first day he was a
suspect,'' Lee said. ``There were a lot of things that kept leading
(us) back to Estrade. We don't have an eyewitness. (But) we have
physical evidence in our possession.''
   Hunters discovered Melissa Estrade's remains on Dec. 3 in woods
near Pass Christian, Miss.
   Estrade had said his daughter disappeared after he dropped her
off at a Metairie day camp Aug. 3. A staff member at the day camp
reported Melissa missing when she failed to show up for a roll call.
   Estrade is divorced from Melissa's mother, Sharon Smith, who had
hired a psychic to try to find her daughter.
   An autopsy and examination by forensic experts have so far failed
to determine how the girl died, but the effort continues, Coroner
Robert Treuting said.
