<HEAD>Two Die in Plane Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENA PARK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A single-engine airplane crashed into a
grocery store warehouse Saturday, killing the pilot and a passenger
but causing no injuries to people on the ground, authorities said.
   The plane hit an unused building at a Lucky Stores warehouse
complex shortly after noon and the two men aboard apparently died on
impact, said police dispatcher Hado Sanders. The victims' names were
withheld.
