<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gang member aiming at a member of a rival
gang opened fire inside a crowded mall, fatally wounding a
16-year-old bystander, police said Saturday.
   In other gang-related shootings, a reputed 27-year-old gang
member was killed while walking with his girlfriend and two
17-year-olds were wounded near the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum.
   Sergio Alpuche, 16, was shopping at a mall in Panorama City, 15
miles northwest of downtown Los Angeles, on Friday when he was hit
by a bullet intended for a San Fernando Valley gang member, police
Detective Paul Stewart said.
   Alpuche died at Holy Cross Medical Center on Saturday.
   The intended victim was fighting with a rival gang member among
the crowd of holiday shoppers when one of the rival's friends fired
a handgun, Stewart said. The gunman was in his early 20s, he added.
No arrests had been made by Saturday afternoon.
   Meanwhile, a reputed gang member strolling with his girlfriend
was gunned down by rivals at 11:20 p.m. Friday, said sheriff's
Deputy Roger Hom. The girlfriend was unharmed.
   Two carloads of gang members confronted Terrance Carl Kennedy as
he walked late Friday night in a southwest Los Angeles neighborhood
and one man shot Kennedy three times, sheriff's Deputy Roger Hom
said.
   Kennedy was pronounced dead 30 minutes later.
   The two youths wounded in the shooting near the Coliseum were hit
by the same bullet as they rode in the back seat of a car, police
said. They were both hospitalized in stable condition. The driver
and front-seat passenger were unhurt.
</TEXT>
